                <div class="tab-content">
                    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab-script">
                        <div class="js-script-content-wrapper top-margin-script markdown-content">
                                                                                        <a href="https://github.com/knpuniversity/symfony2-rest/edit/master/knpu/episode1/tightening-up-response.md" target="_blank" class="btn btn-default btn-circle pull-right js-tooltip" title="Edit on GitHub"><span class="fa fa-pencil"></span></a>
                                                                    <p>This endpoint is missing two teeny-tiny details.</p>
<h2 id="setting-content-type-application-json">Setting Content-Type: application/json <a class="headerlink" href="tightening-up-response#setting-content-type-application-json" title="Permalink to this headline"><i class="fa fa-link" aria-hidden="true"></i></a></h2>
<p>First, we're returning JSON, but the Response <code>Content-Type</code> is still advertising
that we're returning <code>text/html</code>. That's a bummer, and will probably confuse some
clients, like jQuery's AJAX function.</p>
<p>It's easy to fix anyways: set <code>new Response</code> to a <code>$response</code> variable
like we did earlier and call <code>$response-&gt;headers-&gt;set()</code> with <code>Content-Type</code>
and <code>application/json</code>:</p>
<p><div class="code-block-wrapper" data-code-block-guid="41d08fe64b">
