<p>Then re-run:</p>
<pre><code class="language-bash"><div class="line">php testing.php</div></code></pre>
<p>Woh! That exploded! This is Symfony's HTML exception page. It <em>is</em> our 404
error, but it's in HTML instead of JSON. Why? Internally, Symfony has a
request format, which defaults to <code>html</code>. If you change that to <code>json</code>, you'll
get JSON errors. If you're curious about this, google for <code>Symfony request _format</code>.</p>
<p>But I'll show you this later in the series. And we'll go one step further
to <em>completely</em> control the format of our errors. And it will be awesome.</p>
<p>Change the URL in <code>testing.php</code> back to the real nickname.</p>
